  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Search Assets&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Pre-conditions&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The user does not need to be logged in, but may search as an anonymous user&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        One or more assets have been added to RAM through the &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../extend.rup_abd/guidances/toolmentors/submit_asset_draft_ram_28AF53CF.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_Hd8I8PAQEdqqlaqy6gs-Sg&quot;>Submitting Asset Draft using RAM&lt;/a> scenario&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Objectives&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The user searches for assets using the techniques below:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        keywords&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        facets on the repository by which the assets have been categorized&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        advanced search options, on specific metadata elements&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        tags&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The search scope can be the entire repository or with the result list. The search scope is always governed by the&#xD;
    user's permissions.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&lt;img height=&quot;170&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/searchassets1.gif&quot; width=&quot;404&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    &lt;img height=&quot;140&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/searchassets2.gif&quot; width=&quot;201&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img height=&quot;170&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/searchassets3.gif&quot; width=&quot;200&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Steps for Web UI&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Click on the &lt;strong>Search for Assets&lt;/strong> tab&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        There are several ways to search, including: â€¢&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li style=&quot;LIST-STYLE-TYPE: none&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;ul>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Keyword:&lt;/strong> enter a word and search metadata and also artifact content&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Filter:&lt;/strong> select one of the filters such as Asset Type, State, Teamspace, and others&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Advanced:&lt;/strong> enter values to search on specific metadata elements, or for specific phrases&#xD;
                and such&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
            &lt;li>&#xD;
                &lt;strong>Tag:&lt;/strong> use customized tag values to search for assets&#xD;
            &lt;/li>&#xD;
        &lt;/ul>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;h4>&#xD;
    Post-conditions&#xD;
&lt;/h4>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The result list is delivered for the user to browse and evaluate assets&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The result list contents are constrained by the user's permissions&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>More Information&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Please see the Rational Asset Manager related sections on developerWorks.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
